The paper deals with algorithms and complexity theory, specifically in the areas of data structures and computational geometry. The main problem studied is 3SUM, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the variant 3XOR, which involves bit-wise xor instead of integer summation, and this falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves listing triangles in a graph, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and can also be seen as a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses tools from pseudorandomness, which is a topic in complexity theory and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
